  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help Selaravo Saving Club to re organize as a cooperative and offer their services to the whole community. More families are losing their crops and income due to flooding during the cyclone season as a result of climate change and increased logging. The group plans to organize root crop and commodities market to give families opportunity to earn money to use for paying school fees. An agriculture expert will give talks on the farming techniques, crop season and yields in relation to the climate and the general environment of the village and the market opportunities. Some flood tolerant plants will be trialed as well.</narrative>
